description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.⛳️

Super Slow Motion là gì?  
Trước tiên, cần nói qua về kỹ thuật quay phim chậm hay Slow motion trên điện thoại. Slow motion hiểu đơn giản là hiệu ứng video mà các chuyển động của hình ảnh vật thể chậm hơn nhiều lần so với thực tế.

Ví dụ một sự việc diễn ra trong vòng 1 giây được camera ghi lại, khi sử dụng hiệu ứng slow motion sẽ bị làm chậm và kéo dài lên đến 10 giây. Để làm được điều này camera phải có khả năng ghi lại hình ảnh nhanh hơn gấp nhiều lần tương ứng, sau đó phát lại với tốc độ chậm hơn.
Xperia XZs sử dụng cảm biến 19 MP Exmor RS cùng công nghệ Motion Eye mới. Đây cũng là cảm biến đầu tiên trên thế giới tích hợp sẵn bộ nhớ trong. Nhờ công nghệ này mà camera sau của XZs có khả năng quay slowmotion với tốc độ là 960fps.

We describe us as creators. But what makes us different from each other?
It's the way how we see the World. How we composite. How we shoot. What stories we tell. It's all about the story. 

We are indie filmmakers. Indie doesn't mean "Indiana" or "Indian", it's a title - Independent. 

Everyone has a story which deserves to be told. And my job as an indie filmmaker is to tell it in the best possible visual way using the art of cinematography language. 

It's all about the light. Composition. Emotions and colours. Exposure. And the most important - The Story.

My weapons are Blackmagic Design Pocket Cinema Camera 4K ( BMPCC4K ), paired with MFT lenses of Lumix 12-35 and legendary portrait god Helios 44-2 58mm f/2 having the best bokeh. I use DJI Mavic 2 Pro drone to make aerial footage having solid quality, DJI Ronin S handheld gimbal stabilizer with dual handle grip and a little boy - DJI Osmo Mobile 3. All my post production and color grade are made in Davinci Resolve Studio Version.

description:
Mostly testing games I’m interested in, from a somewhat technical point of view, because if there’s something I enjoy and love about PC gaming is flexibility and customization in our games, and tweak stuff to make them run as good as possible given certain hardware specs.

Videos have Timestamps, feel free to jump to the section you want to see.

PC Specs will always be in the video Description.

I'm left handed, so I tend to put a lot on emphasis on keybinds and control setups, even if I'm playing a particular game with Gamepad, it's still important to check those Controls.

I don't do requests, I play/test what I enjoy, there's always too many games coming out, no time for everything :P

These videos aren't "reviews", more like first "technical" impressions and Basic Testing, tweaking Settings if necessary.

Stick to English for the comments, I can answer stuff in Spanish too, but yeah best to stick to what most people understand.

Hope you enjoy your stay : )

Most of the videos have been taken at European Tour events – mostly UK events - though sometimes I venture out as far as Denmark, Turkey and most recently Australia. All the videos are taken during practice days or pro-ams and are never taken during the tournament days.
